In this study, we explored the dynamics of Chlamydia transmission using a fractional order compartmental model within the Caputo framework. The model, validated as biologically accurate, incorporates six categories and provides a positive, bounded, unique solution. We determined the basic reproduction number \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$(R_0)$$\end{document}, establishing the local stability of the Disease-Free Equilibrium (DFE) and the global stability of the Endemic Equilibrium (EE).

